name: Ike Osenberg
bio: Hi! I'm from just North of Philadelphia, I'm a 3rd year Computer Science and Musical Studies major, and Linguistics minor, and I'm a leader of Oberlin Open Source! I'm working on a few long term projects right now, including a Workchart generator for my dining co-op (Pyle) and a structure-overhaul mod for Minecraft. I also teach ToadsCo (an ExCo about herpetology), I work as an RA in Burton and as a technology consultant at the CIT Help Desk, and I am a Membership Coordinator for Pyle Co-op.

projects.name: Workchart Generator
projects.description: Builds a workchart off of a set of co-opers and availabilites read from a Google Form

projects.name: The Polis Project
projects.description: A Minecraft Mod which adds more and more complex populated structures, as well as roads spanning the world which connect structures.
